  "text": "The CNRM-CM global coupled model used in this study is derived from the CMIP5 version described by Voldoire et al. (2013) . The ARPEGE-Climate atmosphere component is version 6.1.0, which benefits from a new prognostic convection scheme (PCMT; [CITATION_1] and Guérémy (2011)), ozone and quasi-biennal oscillation parameterizations (Cariolle and Déqué, 1986; [CITATION_2] and an increased vertical resolution of 91 levels. [CITATION_3] included in the SURFEX v7.3 surface modelling platform, and the sea ice component is an updated version of the GELATO sea ice model (Salas y Melia,",
